  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. To express the value of the property in terms of the property tax, the given equation must be solved for <span class=\"italic\">P</span>. Multiplying both sides of the equation by 100 gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"100 T equals, P minus 40,000\"></span>. Adding 40,000 to both sides of the equation gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"100 T plus 40,000, equals P\"></span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"P equals, 100 T plus 40,000\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect and may result from multiplying 40,000 by 0.01, then subtracting 400 from, instead of adding 400 to, the left-hand side of the equation. Choice B is incorrect and may result from multiplying 40,000 by 0.01. Choice C is incorrect and may result from subtracting instead of adding 40,000 from the left-hand side of the equation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
